VW-owned Spanish carmaker Seat and Cosmopolitan magazine have come under fire on Twitter after teaming up to create a car specifically for women. According to CNN, critics are accusing the companies of blatant gender stereotyping. VW-owned Spanish carmaker Seat and Cosmopolitan magazine have come under fire on Twitter after teaming up to create a car specifically for women. According to CNN, critics are accusing the companies of blatant gender stereotyping.